Here you can find a description of the UI functionalities common to all tabs of the Settings service, for example to filter data or customize tables.

## Toolbar actions
![](data:image/png;base64,)

The toolbar displayed at the top-right of the page allows to perform common actions, listed in the following table:

**Icon**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,) or ![](data:image/png;base64,)

Navigate between result pages.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Open the filters bar. For more information, see [Filtering data](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-common-functionalities#filtering-data) below.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Configure the table columns. For more information, see [Customizing the results table](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-common-functionalities#customizing-the-results-table) below.

## Filtering data
This function allows to apply filters to the displayed data, and update the table in real time.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the top-right corner of the page to open the filters bar. The **Add filter **button is displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Add filter **to expand the filtering options. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Se the required filters and click **Apply **to confirm. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

The applied filters are displayed at the top of the table. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to remove a filter.

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) again to remove all filters and close the filters bar.

## Customizing the results table
This function allows to select which columns to display in the results table.

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) in the top-right corner of the page. The **Configure Columns **panel appears:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the columns that you would like to see in the results table.

- Drag the selected columns to the desired position using the icon  ![](data:image/png;base64,).

- Click **Configure **to save. The selected columns are now visible in the results table.

> Tip

It is possible to resize table columns by moving the column separator.

> Tip

Click **Reset **in the top-right corner of the panel to restore the default configuration of the table.
